WEBVTT

1
00:00:41.250 --> 00:00:43.252
[Insects chittering]

2
00:00:46.714 --> 00:00:49.508
- [Car approaching]
- [Brakes squeaking]

3
00:01:02.647 --> 00:01:05.858
[Car doors open. close]

4
00:01:37.848 --> 00:01:40.101
[Dog barking]

5
00:01:40.184 --> 00:01:41.394
[Whispering] Someone's home.

6
00:01:43.229 --> 00:01:44.939
Supposed to be on vacation.

7
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:48.943
Fuck it. we're here now.

8
00:02:16.554 --> 00:02:18.931
- What are you doing in my house?
- [Wendy] Kyle?

9
00:02:19.015 --> 00:02:20.808
- Dad. Morn!
- Go.

10
00:02:29.025 --> 00:02:30.359
[Siren chirps]

11
00:02:41.787 --> 00:02:44.582
[Helicopter whirring]

12
00:03:12.151 --> 00:03:14.231
House smelled of death
the second we opened the door.

13
00:03:14.278 --> 00:03:17.531
The rook is still in the bathroom.
coughing up lunch.

14
00:03:18.991 --> 00:03:21.202
I don't know if it's about these two
or about the kid.

15
00:03:23.204 --> 00:03:24.747
What kid?

16
00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:26.957
I thought he was dead
until he took a breath.

17
00:03:27.041 --> 00:03:28.584
The paramedics have him.

18
00:03:29.835 --> 00:03:33.506
Hey. I hear you're leaving the department.
Is that true. Joe?

19
00:03:37.301 --> 00:03:39.136
Man. you're not even 50.

20
00:03:40.638 --> 00:03:42.556
What. you hit the lottery or something?

21
00:03:44.558 --> 00:03:47.561
Sometimes you just know.
You should-should go canvass.

22
00:04:02.785 --> 00:04:04.787
[Siren wailing]

23
00:04:10.543 --> 00:04:14.255
[Reporter on TV] A man in larchmont took
his dog on their normal morning stroll.

24
00:04:14.338 --> 00:04:18.175
something he'd done for years. only this
time he found himself being drawn into

25
00:04:18.259 --> 00:04:21.262
what can only be called
a very gruesome scene.

26
00:04:21.345 --> 00:04:23.222
On his walk. the man noticed

27
00:04:23.305 --> 00:04:27.017
that Nicholas and Wendy gervich's
front door was left partially open.

28
00:04:27.101 --> 00:04:31.313
Being friends with the owners of the home.
he decided to investigate.

29
00:04:31.397 --> 00:04:36.193
Once inside. he found two people murdered
and their son brutally beaten.

30
00:04:36.277 --> 00:04:38.046
- While we can only speculate...
- Damn shame.

31
00:04:38.070 --> 00:04:40.197
What really happened
in this house last night...

32
00:04:40.281 --> 00:04:41.824
- [Drew] San Diego?
- No.

33
00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:44.326
Heard about that.

34
00:04:45.327 --> 00:04:47.288
- Damn shame.
- That's what I said.

35
00:04:47.371 --> 00:04:48.747
[Chuckling]

36
00:04:51.792 --> 00:04:53.752
You still back there watching the game?

37
00:04:53.836 --> 00:04:57.256
Well. the padres lost.
I got caught watching the news.

38
00:04:57.339 --> 00:04:59.550
Lloyd. you know nothing good
comes from the news.

39
00:04:59.633 --> 00:05:01.194
- [Lloyd] That's right.
- I have to get this ready

40
00:05:01.218 --> 00:05:03.345
- before Marcus gets here.
- [Doorbell rings]

41
00:05:03.429 --> 00:05:05.181
- [Door opens]
- [Anthony] Hey. hey. hey.

42
00:05:05.264 --> 00:05:07.933
- Hey. family.
- Ha! What's up. drew?

43
00:05:08.017 --> 00:05:10.120
- [Drew] What's going on?
- Look at you. boy. You looking good.

44
00:05:10.144 --> 00:05:12.396
- No. no. you looking better.
- Okay. I'll take that.

45
00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:13.915
- What's up. gorgeous?
- [Tisha] Hey. bro.

46
00:05:13.939 --> 00:05:15.375
- Come here.
- [Tisha] Which way we gonna go?

47
00:05:15.399 --> 00:05:16.734
Come on. now.

48
00:05:16.817 --> 00:05:18.378
- How are you doing?
- [Drew] Good to see you.

49
00:05:18.402 --> 00:05:22.156
Pastor. I'm sure I can find that scripture
for you no problem. Okay?

50
00:05:22.239 --> 00:05:23.449
All right. bye.

51
00:05:24.492 --> 00:05:26.619
[All chattering]

52
00:05:26.702 --> 00:05:29.097
- Hey. how are you doing?
- Who were you talking to. the pastor?

53
00:05:29.121 --> 00:05:30.515
- Apparently.
- [Drew] What's up. bro?

54
00:05:30.539 --> 00:05:32.142
- What's up. man? What's up. dad?
- Good to see you.

55
00:05:32.166 --> 00:05:33.226
- Hey. son.
- How you feeling?

56
00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:34.418
I'm all right.

57
00:05:34.502 --> 00:05:35.878
- What's up. mom?
- Hey. baby.

58
00:05:35.961 --> 00:05:37.129
- I'm good.
- Hey. Terry.

59
00:05:37.213 --> 00:05:38.380
[Terry] The food looks good.

60
00:05:38.464 --> 00:05:39.733
- What's up. tisha?
- How are you?

61
00:05:39.757 --> 00:05:42.760
Lloyd. Marcus is gonna be late
for his own party.

62
00:05:42.843 --> 00:05:44.803
Has anybody talked to Marcus?

63
00:05:44.970 --> 00:05:46.472
[Anne] Four years sober.

64
00:05:48.891 --> 00:05:51.101
I just keep waiting for it to slip away.

65
00:05:52.645 --> 00:05:55.272
- [Phone buzzing]
- But I keep reminding myself

66
00:05:55.356 --> 00:05:58.067
to stay focused on my greatest good.

67
00:05:59.485 --> 00:06:00.486
[People clapping]

68
00:06:06.659 --> 00:06:09.328
Marcus. would you like to join in?

69
00:06:11.789 --> 00:06:13.624
Uh. sure.

70
00:06:15.167 --> 00:06:18.462
You all know
I've had trouble staying sober. Um...

71
00:06:20.673 --> 00:06:22.800
But I think I finally
found a reason to pull through.

72
00:06:23.801 --> 00:06:27.388
That's good. Marcus.
Would you care to let us know the reason?

73
00:06:28.597 --> 00:06:30.474
- I got a new job.
- Oh.

74
00:06:30.558 --> 00:06:34.228
Yeah. my dad got me this great new job.
I'm gonna be driving buses for the city.

75
00:06:35.896 --> 00:06:37.731
So hopefully. I'll get my shit together.

76
00:06:37.815 --> 00:06:38.815
[Chuckles]

77
00:06:44.655 --> 00:06:45.656
[Line ringing]

78
00:06:50.828 --> 00:06:53.247
Uh. hey. Wanda.
it's Eva returning your call.

79
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:56.749
Mm-hmm.

80
00:06:58.210 --> 00:06:59.210
Mm-hmm.

81
00:07:00.713 --> 00:07:02.214
Yeah. Hey.

82
00:07:02.298 --> 00:07:03.591
[Door closes]

83
00:07:03.674 --> 00:07:06.510
Yo. Marcus.
Hey. where were you. man?

84
00:07:08.387 --> 00:07:11.015
- You know.
- Oh. that's right. All right. I got you.

85
00:07:11.098 --> 00:07:13.225
Eva. Hey. how you doing?

86
00:07:13.309 --> 00:07:15.894
- Uh. tisha's in here waiting on you.
- Got to go. Okay.

87
00:07:15.978 --> 00:07:17.896
[Anthony] She's a nurse over at
the cathedral.

88
00:07:17.980 --> 00:07:20.399
Tish and she are good friends.
They're good friends together.

89
00:07:20.482 --> 00:07:22.276
- Mm-hmm.
- Eva. this is Marcus.

90
00:07:22.359 --> 00:07:23.819
Marcus. this is Eva.

91
00:07:23.902 --> 00:07:25.613
- Hi. Hey.

92
00:07:27.990 --> 00:07:29.110
No. no. this is the brother.

93
00:07:29.158 --> 00:07:31.198
This is the brother
that tish was telling you about.

94
00:07:32.786 --> 00:07:36.290
Oh. uh. tisha just said
I was here for dinner.

95
00:07:38.167 --> 00:07:40.252
- She did?
- Mm-hmm.

96
00:07:40.336 --> 00:07:43.088
Okay. come on in.
Food-food's ready. It's hot.

97
00:07:43.172 --> 00:07:44.590
Sorry.

98
00:07:44.673 --> 00:07:46.884
- Now. Eva? Can you do me a favor?
- Mm-hmm?

99
00:07:46.967 --> 00:07:49.279
Can you not tell tish about this moment
that we just had out here?

100
00:07:49.303 --> 00:07:52.014
- Just keep it between us.
- Oh. I'm gonna get you in trouble.

101
00:07:52.097 --> 00:07:53.557
[Chuckles]

102
00:08:02.983 --> 00:08:03.984
Thank you.

103
00:08:05.319 --> 00:08:07.321
[All laughing. chattering]

104
00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:31.261
[Laughing. chattering continues]

105
00:08:45.275 --> 00:08:47.569
- She's really nice.
- [Sports chatter on TV]

106
00:08:47.653 --> 00:08:51.615
And tish told me that she invited her
here to meet you.

107
00:08:51.699 --> 00:08:56.995
But yet here you are. in a room
full of men that you already know.

108
00:08:57.079 --> 00:08:58.455
[Marcus] Uh. tsk...

109
00:08:58.539 --> 00:09:00.541
Can y'all tell your mother
to mind her business?

110
00:09:00.624 --> 00:09:04.128
Uh. excuse me. son.
You are my business.

111
00:09:04.211 --> 00:09:05.504
You're my baby.

112
00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:10.300
So does anybody
want to help with the dishes?

113
00:09:11.593 --> 00:09:14.304
Nobody? Really?

114
00:09:14.388 --> 00:09:15.388
Pop?

115
00:09:16.724 --> 00:09:17.724
Pop?

116
00:09:19.852 --> 00:09:22.104
- [Lloyd] Hey. Marcus.
- Yeah?

117
00:09:22.187 --> 00:09:24.732
Would you please get
your old daddy a beer?

118
00:09:24.815 --> 00:09:26.567
Oh. my goodness. you too. pop?

119
00:09:26.650 --> 00:09:29.570
Yeah. Marcus. Get your dad a beer.

120
00:09:29.653 --> 00:09:31.989
[Chattering]

121
00:09:32.072 --> 00:09:34.074
- [Lloyd] Be cool.
- [Chuckles]

122
00:09:34.158 --> 00:09:36.326
- What's up. y'all?
- Hey.

123
00:09:37.327 --> 00:09:40.164
[Marcus] Oh. man. that food was good.

124
00:09:40.247 --> 00:09:41.247
[Clears throat]

125
00:09:45.294 --> 00:09:48.088
You know what? Let me go see
if I can find some more dishes. okay?

126
00:09:49.882 --> 00:09:50.883
[Eva] Mm-hmm.

127
00:09:57.473 --> 00:09:59.183
You have a good time tonight?

128
00:09:59.266 --> 00:10:00.267
Yeah. I did.

129
00:10:01.477 --> 00:10:04.104
- My mama can burn.
- Mm-hmm.

130
00:10:04.188 --> 00:10:05.481
You?

131
00:10:10.319 --> 00:10:13.280
So you're starting a new job tomorrow.

132
00:10:14.281 --> 00:10:15.282
You nervous?

133
00:10:16.283 --> 00:10:19.119
- Little bit. yeah.
- Some advice?

134
00:10:20.788 --> 00:10:23.540
Try not to think about failing.

135
00:10:23.624 --> 00:10:25.459
Just let things row.

136
00:10:25.542 --> 00:10:27.461
[Dishes clatter]

137
00:10:28.796 --> 00:10:31.423
- Hey. yo. Terry.
- Huh?

138
00:10:31.507 --> 00:10:33.801
- Terry!
- Coming. coming. coming.

139
00:10:33.884 --> 00:10:34.884
[Grunts]

140
00:10:36.637 --> 00:10:40.849
Hey. give that to pop.
I'm. uh. gonna help out with the dishes.

141
00:10:42.100 --> 00:10:43.685
You don't do dishes.

142
00:10:43.769 --> 00:10:47.314
Dry-snitching.
You must be the baby brother.

143
00:10:47.397 --> 00:10:48.565
I like her.

144
00:10:50.609 --> 00:10:52.319
- Oh. yeah. I'm...
- [Eva chuckles]

145
00:10:54.947 --> 00:10:56.240
[Both clear throat]

146
00:10:58.700 --> 00:11:00.452
You know. for the record.

147
00:11:00.536 --> 00:11:04.414
I don't have anything to do
with the whole set-up thing.

148
00:11:04.498 --> 00:11:07.292
- Blind date...
- I can tell.

149
00:11:07.376 --> 00:11:10.379
- You've been avoiding me all night.
- No. I wasn't avoiding you.

150
00:11:10.462 --> 00:11:12.714
I just didn't want you to feel pressured.

151
00:11:12.798 --> 00:11:14.174
I appreciate that.

152
00:11:16.051 --> 00:11:17.469
That's the worst feeling.

153
00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:19.972
You being pressured?

154
00:11:20.055 --> 00:11:22.057
Yeah. I feel like that all the time.

155
00:11:23.642 --> 00:11:24.643
By who?

156
00:11:34.444 --> 00:11:38.448
Tish. um. had a lot of nice things
to say about you.

157
00:11:39.741 --> 00:11:42.369
I should have figured something was up.

158
00:11:42.452 --> 00:11:43.704
Tish talks a lot.

159
00:11:44.955 --> 00:11:46.081
She does.

160
00:11:46.164 --> 00:11:47.708
[Both laugh]

161
00:11:51.461 --> 00:11:53.797
Did tish tell you anything about me?

162
00:11:56.174 --> 00:11:57.968
I mean. no. Like I said.

163
00:11:58.051 --> 00:12:01.597
you were... a complete surprise.

164
00:12:04.850 --> 00:12:06.852
Did she tell you anything about me?

165
00:12:09.938 --> 00:12:13.901
Life's been hard for you.
but you keep trying.

166
00:12:18.614 --> 00:12:21.158
I lost my two oldest brothers
to la. Life.

167
00:12:22.576 --> 00:12:25.370
One to drugs. the other to gang violence.

168
00:12:25.454 --> 00:12:26.955
- I'm sorry to hear that.
- Mm.

169
00:12:29.374 --> 00:12:34.212
I kind of gave up on brothers who were
trying to get themselves together.

170
00:12:34.296 --> 00:12:38.467
until I realized we're all trying
to get ourselves together.

171
00:12:42.262 --> 00:12:45.098
I haven't dated in a while.

172
00:12:45.182 --> 00:12:49.811
It's hard when you're a nurse.
and I want to find a good brother.

173
00:12:52.397 --> 00:12:55.609
And now I sound desperate.

174
00:12:55.692 --> 00:12:57.736
- So now I'm shutting up. [Chuckles]
- No. you...

175
00:12:57.819 --> 00:12:58.946
[Chuckles]

176
00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:06.703
Let me ask you something.

177
00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:11.416
Are you always this honest?

178
00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:14.586
Surprises are for birthdays and Christmas.

179
00:13:15.587 --> 00:13:17.965
Not when you're trying
to get to know someone.

180
00:13:21.385 --> 00:13:22.385
Hmm.

181
00:13:29.017 --> 00:13:32.980
So. uh. I guess this is good night.

182
00:13:33.063 --> 00:13:36.650
Or this is when you ask me for my number.

183
00:13:36.733 --> 00:13:41.113
555-6433.
Tish gave it to me when we were...

184
00:13:41.196 --> 00:13:43.740
She texted it to me
when we were cleaning up the kitchen.

185
00:13:43.824 --> 00:13:45.200
Of course she did.

186
00:13:45.283 --> 00:13:47.244
- Yeah. Told you she got a big mouth.
- Yup.

187
00:13:49.413 --> 00:13:51.540
You should use it.

188
00:13:51.623 --> 00:13:52.624
Yes. ma'am.

189
00:13:54.459 --> 00:13:56.461
- I should go. Mm-hmm.
- All right.

190
00:13:56.545 --> 00:13:57.963
- Hey. get home safe.
- I will.

191
00:13:58.046 --> 00:13:59.172
- Bye-bye.
- Good night.

192
00:13:59.256 --> 00:14:00.257
Good night.

193
00:14:04.302 --> 00:14:05.303
[Car door closes]

194
00:14:07.806 --> 00:14:08.932
[Door opens]

195
00:14:13.520 --> 00:14:15.022
I can drive. man.

196
00:14:15.105 --> 00:14:16.940
Let me drive.
You're drunk off your ass.

197
00:14:17.024 --> 00:14:18.751
- I'm gonna get him home.
- You're gonna take him?

198
00:14:18.775 --> 00:14:20.318
Yup. I got him. I got him. pop.

199
00:14:20.402 --> 00:14:22.487
No. no. you're going with Marcus.

200
00:14:22.571 --> 00:14:24.406
- Here you go.
- All right. then. You got him?

201
00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:26.283
- Yup. I got him.
- Love y'all.

202
00:14:26.366 --> 00:14:28.469
It ain't cool getting drunk
like that in front of Marcus.

203
00:14:28.493 --> 00:14:30.328
All right. I love you. pop.

204
00:14:30.412 --> 00:14:33.123
- Mm-hmm. you too.
- Goddamn.

205
00:14:33.206 --> 00:14:34.791
Wait. wait. wait. wait.

206
00:14:34.875 --> 00:14:38.420
Don't throw up on my walkway.
Uh—uh. uh-uh.

207
00:14:41.423 --> 00:14:43.091
- I love you. man.
- Hey. I love you too.

208
00:14:44.718 --> 00:14:46.053
- [Snoring]
- [Door opens]

209
00:14:51.349 --> 00:14:52.976
You're not here much. are you?

210
00:14:53.060 --> 00:14:54.519
[Sighs]

211
00:14:57.230 --> 00:14:58.857
I stay at rhea's most of the time.

212
00:15:00.442 --> 00:15:02.402
She won't stay here.

213
00:15:02.486 --> 00:15:04.362
You should try cleaning up
every now and then.

214
00:15:04.446 --> 00:15:08.075
You feeling good
about yourself. huh? [Grunts]

215
00:15:09.493 --> 00:15:11.119
- Yeah. I guess.
- Hmm.

216
00:15:13.288 --> 00:15:16.708
You're sober. You got a job.

217
00:15:18.043 --> 00:15:19.753
Shit is looking up. man.

218
00:15:19.836 --> 00:15:22.547
- You're sounding jealous.
- [Chuckles]

219
00:15:22.631 --> 00:15:27.094
I guess mama praying to Jesus
and his cousins finally worked.

220
00:15:28.845 --> 00:15:30.347
You know. you like a cat.

221
00:15:31.348 --> 00:15:33.058
Black cat. [Chuckles]

222
00:15:35.102 --> 00:15:36.770
You got nine goddamn lives.

223
00:15:36.853 --> 00:15:38.063
You ain't happy for me?

224
00:15:38.146 --> 00:15:39.981
Marcus. sit down.

225
00:15:40.065 --> 00:15:42.567
I think if I keep looking up.
I'ma throw up.

226
00:15:42.651 --> 00:15:43.902
[Marcus chuckles]

227
00:15:51.409 --> 00:15:52.452
You know...

228
00:15:57.374 --> 00:15:59.626
It's like you and I traded places.

229
00:16:01.378 --> 00:16:02.754
I lost my job. man.

230
00:16:02.838 --> 00:16:06.049
The gas company?
That job's for life.

231
00:16:07.884 --> 00:16:10.011
Corporate bullshit.

232
00:16:10.095 --> 00:16:12.848
Me and some folks
got caught in the middle.

233
00:16:12.931 --> 00:16:14.516
It's been a few months now.

234
00:16:14.599 --> 00:16:15.892
You'll come through.

235
00:16:18.770 --> 00:16:20.772
I gotta do more than come through.

236
00:16:24.401 --> 00:16:25.819
Rhea broke up with me.

237
00:16:27.404 --> 00:16:29.531
Drew Jr. needs books for college. man.

238
00:16:29.614 --> 00:16:32.409
These bills. they're coming out
of my ass right now. You know?

239
00:16:32.492 --> 00:16:35.704
Like. shit is real rough right now.

240
00:16:35.787 --> 00:16:37.455
Like for real. this shit is rough.

241
00:16:42.377 --> 00:16:43.712
I'ma be honest.

242
00:16:45.213 --> 00:16:47.257
Nobody really liked rhea anyway.

243
00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:49.050
So you might have made out on that one.

244
00:16:49.134 --> 00:16:50.135
[Both chuckle]

245
00:16:51.344 --> 00:16:55.348
As soon as I get paid.
I'll hit you up with some money.

246
00:16:56.892 --> 00:16:58.977
When you get paid.

247
00:16:59.060 --> 00:17:01.813
you're gonna have your fair share
of people to pay back.

248
