1204
01:18:39.132 --> 01:18:41.342
Whether it be yourjunkie-ass brother.

1205
01:18:41.426 --> 01:18:46.973
who I heard was taking dicks for bags.
or whoever the fuck it is.

1206
01:18:47.056 --> 01:18:49.601
- I don't give a fuck.
- Calm down.

1207
01:18:55.982 --> 01:18:56.982
Drew.

1208
01:18:59.903 --> 01:19:04.324
If Marcus is behind this shit.
your ass got decisions. bro.

1209
01:19:05.742 --> 01:19:10.204
Because it's all three of us
against every-fucking-body

1210
01:19:10.288 --> 01:19:13.291
or it's you against me and ai.

1211
01:19:19.255 --> 01:19:21.799
Yeah. You think this is funny.
Okay. clap all you want.

1212
01:19:26.888 --> 01:19:28.431
Nobody fucks with my family.

1213
01:19:33.311 --> 01:19:35.396
Whoa. You gonna do me like that?

1214
01:19:35.480 --> 01:19:37.148
- Hmm.
- When all this shit is your fault?

1215
01:19:39.692 --> 01:19:41.027
Shut the fuck up!

1216
01:19:42.654 --> 01:19:44.906
Shut the fuck up! [Echoes]

1217
01:19:44.989 --> 01:19:46.991
[Car doors open. close]

1218
01:19:57.502 --> 01:19:58.920
Fuck!

1219
01:20:08.930 --> 01:20:10.598
[Glass shattering]

1220
01:20:12.767 --> 01:20:15.520
Wait. What are you guys doing in my house?

1221
01:20:21.192 --> 01:20:22.318
- Dad?

1222
01:20:22.402 --> 01:20:24.612
Dad. Mom!

1223
01:20:24.696 --> 01:20:27.824
[Wendy] Honey. what's wrong?
Nicholas. Kyle. God...

1224
01:20:27.907 --> 01:20:29.200
[Screaming]

1225
01:20:30.201 --> 01:20:31.619
[Clattering]

1226
01:20:31.703 --> 01:20:33.543
- [Wendy screams]
- [Stacy] Stay the fuck down!

1227
01:20:38.584 --> 01:20:41.129
- [Blows landing]
- [Shouting]

1228
01:20:55.143 --> 01:20:58.479
- [Wendy screams. sobs]
- [Gunshots]

1229
01:20:58.563 --> 01:21:00.648
[Stacy]
Yo. what the fuck are you doing?

1230
01:21:00.732 --> 01:21:02.732
[Drew] Search the house.
I'll take care of the kid.

1231
01:21:20.209 --> 01:21:22.712
So why didn't you tell us about it
when you first found out?

1232
01:21:25.214 --> 01:21:29.635
Honestly. I just had a hard time
wrapping my head around what I knew.

1233
01:21:32.638 --> 01:21:35.118
[Terry] What you doing back here. man?
I thought you went home.

1234
01:21:39.729 --> 01:21:41.064
I thought this through.

1235
01:21:42.356 --> 01:21:44.901
I shouldn't go talk to ai and Stacy alone.

1236
01:21:46.110 --> 01:21:48.112
Maybe one of you can go with me.

1237
01:21:55.328 --> 01:21:57.163
You ain't gotta do this alone.

1238
01:22:00.249 --> 01:22:01.751
That's what we're here for.

1239
01:22:04.087 --> 01:22:05.254
I love you. man.

1240
01:22:07.507 --> 01:22:08.800
Always here for you.

1241
01:22:14.347 --> 01:22:16.557
[Scoffs] Seriously.

1242
01:22:16.641 --> 01:22:19.185
- [Laughing]
- [Terry] Y'all two. man.

1243
01:22:41.374 --> 01:22:45.128
Yeah. Marie says she'll take over
the next few days. Yeah.

1244
01:22:45.211 --> 01:22:46.629
Hey. uh. let me call you back.

1245
01:22:46.712 --> 01:22:47.964
All right. bye-bye.

1246
01:22:49.674 --> 01:22:53.136
- Good morning. my love.
- Good morning. sweetheart.

1247
01:22:53.219 --> 01:22:55.680
- How you feeling this morning?
- I'm good. I'm good.

1248
01:22:55.763 --> 01:22:58.975
You know. you should go in.
'cause that place falls apart without you.

1249
01:22:59.058 --> 01:23:01.978
No. we're not in tax season.
so we're good.

1250
01:23:02.061 --> 01:23:04.772
And who told you
to come in here without me. huh?

1251
01:23:04.856 --> 01:23:07.733
Look. I ain't no invalid.

1252
01:23:08.734 --> 01:23:12.113
Although. I did feel a little tired

1253
01:23:12.196 --> 01:23:15.074
when I was trying to make it
over to turn on the radio.

1254
01:23:15.158 --> 01:23:17.618
Could you help me just turn on the radio?

1255
01:23:17.702 --> 01:23:19.203
Oh. so now you need me. huh?

1256
01:23:19.287 --> 01:23:22.456
- Mr. I ain't no invalid.
- [Both laughing]

1257
01:23:23.457 --> 01:23:26.252
You know. you ain't no badass
just 'cause you're turning on the radio.

1258
01:23:26.335 --> 01:23:27.688
I'm the one who had a heart attack.

1259
01:23:27.712 --> 01:23:29.005
- That you did.
- Yeah.

1260
01:23:29.088 --> 01:23:30.488
- You want some coffee?
- Huh? Yeah.

1261
01:23:30.548 --> 01:23:32.758
[Newscaster] ...Stacy Griffin
and his friend al Edwards

1262
01:23:32.842 --> 01:23:36.012
were found murdered this morning
at Stacy's barber shop.

1263
01:23:36.095 --> 01:23:39.390
Sources say police at the scene
seem to strongly believe

1264
01:23:39.473 --> 01:23:41.893
that it was an armed robbery gone wrong...

1265
01:23:41.976 --> 01:23:45.229
That killed both men.
then proceeded to ransack the shop.

1266
01:23:45.313 --> 01:23:47.064
So far there's been no witnesses.

1267
01:23:47.148 --> 01:23:49.358
Now. both men have been
in and out of trouble...

1268
01:23:49.442 --> 01:23:51.444
[Newscaster continues indistinctly]

1269
01:24:07.168 --> 01:24:08.419
[Phone buzzes]

1270
01:24:12.632 --> 01:24:13.883
[Bell tolls]

1271
01:24:15.676 --> 01:24:16.719
[Phone buzzes]

1272
01:24:18.179 --> 01:24:19.931
[Phone buzzes]

1273
01:24:34.946 --> 01:24:35.947
Hey.

1274
01:24:41.369 --> 01:24:43.913
Why'd you get involved
with this shit. drew?

1275
01:24:54.298 --> 01:24:55.716
I got desperate.

1276
01:25:01.055 --> 01:25:02.306
And I was broke.

1277
01:25:07.520 --> 01:25:09.456
I saw how much Marcus
was costing the family. man.

1278
01:25:09.480 --> 01:25:10.773
I didn't want to add to that.

1279
01:25:17.154 --> 01:25:18.197
It was dumb.

1280
01:25:22.952 --> 01:25:25.746
And you're lucky
that you weren't there last night.

1281
01:25:27.081 --> 01:25:28.207
[Scoffs]

1282
01:25:30.042 --> 01:25:34.672
I think Marcus did a really good thing
calling in that tip.

1283
01:25:35.881 --> 01:25:38.009
So-so don't be
too hard on him about that.

1284
01:25:38.092 --> 01:25:40.094
especially since he was trying
to protect you.

1285
01:25:44.890 --> 01:25:46.309
I won't. [Sniffles]

1286
01:25:57.611 --> 01:25:58.863
I'ma take a shower.

1287
01:25:58.946 --> 01:26:00.841
Yeah. I'm gonna lay some
clothes out for you. all right?

1288
01:26:00.865 --> 01:26:03.409
- All right.
- Hey. um. wait a minute.

1289
01:26:18.549 --> 01:26:19.675
[Drew sniffles]

1290
01:26:25.639 --> 01:26:26.891
[Breathing heavily]

1291
01:26:31.645 --> 01:26:32.813
Listen...

1292
01:26:34.565 --> 01:26:37.360
Those dudes being dead
might not be such a bad thing. bro.

1293
01:26:39.028 --> 01:26:40.196
Okay?

1294
01:26:46.369 --> 01:26:47.411
[Sniffles]

1295
01:26:49.789 --> 01:26:50.789
[Exhales] All right.

1296
01:26:57.630 --> 01:27:00.883
Well. at least what had happened to you
wasn't on the news. drew.

1297
01:27:02.968 --> 01:27:05.763
No. it still don't stop them
nosy—ass neighbors from talking.

1298
01:27:05.846 --> 01:27:08.182
- Mm-mm.
- You know the word had got out.

1299
01:27:08.265 --> 01:27:11.102
Mom. I don't care what people saying now.
I got y'all.

1300
01:27:11.185 --> 01:27:12.478
If I didn't. I probably...

1301
01:27:12.561 --> 01:27:14.897
- Did anybody hear from Marcus?
- No.

1302
01:27:14.980 --> 01:27:17.441
What. he didn't call none of y'all?

1303
01:27:17.525 --> 01:27:20.319
- Hey. you talk to him?
- I'll try him again. I'll try him again.

1304
01:27:22.947 --> 01:27:24.657
[Line ringing]

1305
01:27:24.740 --> 01:27:26.283
[Phone buzzing]

1306
01:27:30.830 --> 01:27:32.373
[Buzzing continues]

1307
01:27:42.842 --> 01:27:47.221
You know. Marcus is probably still mad
that al and Stacy attacked him.

1308
01:27:47.304 --> 01:27:49.723
Hmm. Yeah. I would be. too.

1309
01:27:51.350 --> 01:27:53.769
What do you think really happened
with those dudes?

1310
01:27:55.521 --> 01:27:58.315
Well. I think it's like mama said.

1311
01:27:58.399 --> 01:27:59.942
Bad catches up with bad people.

1312
01:28:00.943 --> 01:28:02.903
I'm just glad I ain't go talk to 'em.

1313
01:28:02.987 --> 01:28:06.282
Shit. I might have been there
when they got shot.

1314
01:28:07.616 --> 01:28:11.078
Drew. baby. let me
talk to you for a minute.

1315
01:28:11.162 --> 01:28:12.413
Yes. ma'am.

1316
01:28:14.790 --> 01:28:15.791
What happened?

1317
01:28:17.585 --> 01:28:21.005
I told mama and daddy
that that lawyer might not be a bad idea.

1318
01:28:26.969 --> 01:28:28.220
Coming. mama.

1319
01:28:33.142 --> 01:28:34.810
Terry. let me ask you this. bro.

1320
01:28:37.605 --> 01:28:41.358
Knowing what you know about what drew did.
does that bother you?

1321
01:28:45.863 --> 01:28:46.864
A lot.

1322
01:28:49.950 --> 01:28:51.619
I pray on it every night.

1323
01:28:54.163 --> 01:28:55.873
But praying doesn't change everything.

1324
01:29:00.336 --> 01:29:01.754
[Marcus] Hey. what's up. baby?

1325
01:29:04.507 --> 01:29:07.092
- Hey. Marcus.
- Hey. what's up? I miss you.

1326
01:29:10.346 --> 01:29:12.348
Marcus. have you been drinking?

1327
01:29:14.016 --> 01:29:18.562
Eva. drew's homies. ai and Stacy.
they... they got killed.

1328
01:29:18.646 --> 01:29:21.190
Police say it was a stickup or some shit.

1329
01:29:29.490 --> 01:29:30.574
What do you say?

1330
01:29:31.575 --> 01:29:34.787
Some dirty niggas. e.
Could have been anybody.

1331
01:29:34.870 --> 01:29:37.623
But I know drew was at the house
with Anthony when it happened.

1332
01:29:37.706 --> 01:29:40.334
I know that for sure.

1333
01:29:40.417 --> 01:29:42.479
- I just wanna talk to you. baby.
- Marcus. I don't have...

1334
01:29:42.503 --> 01:29:43.837
I wanna talk to you.

1335
01:29:43.921 --> 01:29:45.548
- I don't...
- I just gotta talk to you.

1336
01:29:47.174 --> 01:29:50.219
I gotta tell you something. Okay?

1337
01:29:50.302 --> 01:29:54.848
And hopefully. it will make you understand
why I tried to protect my brother.

1338
01:29:54.932 --> 01:29:56.684
All right?

1339
01:29:56.767 --> 01:29:59.478
Tish. she ain't tell you
everything about me.

1340
01:30:00.813 --> 01:30:03.357
I was accused of murder. too.
But I ain't kill nobody.

1341
01:30:05.442 --> 01:30:07.361
Dude's name was Dwight Tooley.

1342
01:30:07.444 --> 01:30:10.406
He owed me some dope money.
I went to collect. We got into it.

1343
01:30:10.489 --> 01:30:12.449
Shit got ugly. He hit his head.
Next thing I know.

1344
01:30:12.491 --> 01:30:15.286
police is arresting me
for assault and battery.

1345
01:30:15.369 --> 01:30:18.247
And then two months later.
he dies of a brain aneurysm.

1346
01:30:18.330 --> 01:30:21.292
- An aneurysm can happen at any time.
- Exactly.

1347
01:30:21.375 --> 01:30:23.794
It's the same shit
my lawyer was trying to say.

1348
01:30:23.877 --> 01:30:26.797
but the family. they wasn't trying
to hear me doing a year for assault.

1349
01:30:26.880 --> 01:30:29.174
so they got the judge
to up my sentence to manslaughter.

1350
01:30:29.258 --> 01:30:33.178
They said if we didn't get into the fight.
then he wouldn't have died.

1351
01:30:33.262 --> 01:30:36.765
They put years on my sentence.

1352
01:30:36.849 --> 01:30:38.350
Years I ain't deserve.

1353
01:30:40.686 --> 01:30:43.439
E. if my brother got anything
to do with this...

1354
01:30:45.274 --> 01:30:48.444
That's never gonna sit well with me. ever.

1355
01:30:49.862 --> 01:30:52.823
But I don't want to lose you to this. e.

1356
01:30:52.906 --> 01:30:55.951
I don't want to lose you to this shit.
I don't want to lose you to nothing.

1357
01:31:00.873 --> 01:31:03.125
I'm so sorry this happened to us.

1358
01:31:09.423 --> 01:31:11.008
I love you so much.

1359
01:31:11.091 --> 01:31:12.551
Come back to me. baby.

1360
01:31:13.552 --> 01:31:16.180
God... no. I can't.

1361
01:31:16.263 --> 01:31:18.182
- Come back to me.
- I can't. Not with this...

1362
01:31:18.265 --> 01:31:19.642
Not with this going on.

1363
01:31:19.725 --> 01:31:21.143
[Horn honks]

1364
01:31:23.812 --> 01:31:24.812
[Sighs]

1365
01:31:26.357 --> 01:31:27.775
Really?

1366
01:31:27.858 --> 01:31:30.277
You got a nigga picking you up that quick?

1367
01:31:33.572 --> 01:31:36.492
If that's what you think.

1368
01:31:36.575 --> 01:31:39.119
then you never got
how much I cared about you.

1369
01:31:45.334 --> 01:31:46.627
He's my cousin.

1370
01:31:54.927 --> 01:31:56.220
[Car departs]

1371
01:31:58.222 --> 01:31:59.515
[Knocking on door]

1372
01:32:14.196 --> 01:32:15.864
[Knocking continues]

1373
01:32:20.869 --> 01:32:22.162
What are you doing here?

1374
01:32:23.247 --> 01:32:25.165
I'd like to talk to you
about your brother.

1375
01:32:27.459 --> 01:32:28.293
[High-pitched ringing]

1376
01:32:28.377 --> 01:32:30.772
[Marcus] You're telling me the same gun
that killed Stacy and al

1377
01:32:30.796 --> 01:32:32.476
is the same gun that killed the gerviches?

1378
01:32:32.548 --> 01:32:33.549
[Joe] Yeah.

1379
01:32:34.591 --> 01:32:36.486
Doesn't mean the gun
didn't belong to either of 'em.

1380
01:32:36.510 --> 01:32:38.762
But it wasn't a murder-suicide.

1381
01:32:38.846 --> 01:32:41.056
- Someone else wanted them shut down.
- [Ringing fades]

1382
01:32:41.140 --> 01:32:43.767
Instead of you following leads.
you drop over here with coffee?

1383
01:32:45.060 --> 01:32:47.521
[Chuckles] Yeah. with good reason.

1384
01:32:47.604 --> 01:32:52.401
Those bullets led me back to the night
that they were all brought in.

1385
01:32:54.278 --> 01:32:56.405
Most importantly. drew.

1386
01:32:56.488 --> 01:32:57.740
Why is that?

1387
01:32:57.823 --> 01:33:00.492
Because of how he talked about you.

1388
01:33:00.576 --> 01:33:03.287
He-he mentioned me?

1389
01:33:03.370 --> 01:33:08.834
He never mentioned you by name.
but. uh. wow. you know.

1390
01:33:08.917 --> 01:33:13.005
once he started tearing you apart.
he-he couldn't stop.

1391
01:33:13.088 --> 01:33:16.175
How could you know he was talking
about me? He's got three brothers.

1392
01:33:16.258 --> 01:33:19.595
Only one's an addict and did jail time.

1393
01:33:23.098 --> 01:33:24.475
He covered everything.

1394
01:33:24.558 --> 01:33:26.393
Like what?

1395
01:33:27.394 --> 01:33:29.271
He said he felt like
he was living your life

1396
01:33:29.354 --> 01:33:32.232
now that shit had gotten better for you.

1397
01:33:32.316 --> 01:33:34.359
He lost his job. he lost his girlfriend.

1398
01:33:34.443 --> 01:33:37.362
he was being dragged into
a bullshit murder charge.

1399
01:33:37.446 --> 01:33:40.657
which he-he wasn't mad about.

1400
01:33:40.741 --> 01:33:45.746
But when I asked him
if he was living two lives. boom.

1401
01:33:48.123 --> 01:33:49.666
He went into his brother.

1402
01:33:49.750 --> 01:33:52.503
If you think drew's behind all of this.
then fucking arrest him.

1403
01:33:57.174 --> 01:33:59.176
[Sighs] That would be a waste of time.

1404
01:34:00.719 --> 01:34:04.473
The more missteps you make in
a homicide case. the more messy it gets.

1405
01:34:04.556 --> 01:34:06.725
And I don't...
I don't fucking do messy.

1406
01:34:06.809 --> 01:34:08.769
Like you being here right now ain't messy?

1407
01:34:08.852 --> 01:34:11.271
You know... [clears throat]

1408
01:34:11.355 --> 01:34:13.273
My mother told me when I was a kid

1409
01:34:13.357 --> 01:34:16.068
that the biggest Christian
was probably the biggest sinner

1410
01:34:16.151 --> 01:34:21.114
and that the second they took Jesus
into their heart.

1411
01:34:21.198 --> 01:34:24.201
that's when they could only
see in black and white.

1412
01:34:26.119 --> 01:34:29.498
You know who else is superjudgmental?

1413
01:34:31.542 --> 01:34:33.877
Addicts who get clean.

1414
01:34:34.920 --> 01:34:39.466
The anonymous caller
was someone who wanted a reward.

1415
01:34:39.550 --> 01:34:41.468
someone who wanted to do right.

1416
01:34:43.720 --> 01:34:46.515
There was no reward being offered. Marcus.

1417
01:34:46.598 --> 01:34:48.475
What you trying to say?

1418
01:34:48.559 --> 01:34:50.060
You think it was me?

1419
01:34:53.063 --> 01:34:56.441
I'm just trying to see
where the puzzle pieces fit.

1420
01:34:56.525 --> 01:34:59.111
I'm sorry. bro. It wasn't me.

1421
01:35:01.864 --> 01:35:05.617
My first year as a detective.

1422
01:35:05.701 --> 01:35:08.912
I knew that if I could get information
from a murderer's wife.

1423
01:35:08.996 --> 01:35:11.081
I could close the case.

1424
01:35:12.082 --> 01:35:14.459
But every time I tried to talk to her.
she shut me out.

1425
01:35:14.543 --> 01:35:17.170
I mean. he was abusive. but she was...

1426
01:35:18.755 --> 01:35:20.173
She was ride or die.

1427
01:35:21.675 --> 01:35:24.094
So one day I waited for the husband
to leave and. um...

1428
01:35:27.389 --> 01:35:32.352
I remember I brought her a carton
of her favorite cigarettes.

1429
01:35:32.436 --> 01:35:36.106
And within 20 minutes of sitting
on her couch. she told me everything.

1430
01:35:36.189 --> 01:35:40.777
because I just happened to show up
right after he put hands on her.

1431
01:35:42.362 --> 01:35:47.743
When people have information
that they really wanna share...

1432
01:35:48.952 --> 01:35:51.246
They're hoping that somebody
will coax it out of 'em.

1433
01:35:51.330 --> 01:35:54.374
It is my job to catch them
at the right time.

1434
01:35:55.375 --> 01:35:57.377
Ain't none of that shit my concern.

1435
01:35:58.587 --> 01:36:01.214
Drew was with my brother Anthony
that night.

1436
01:36:03.800 --> 01:36:06.053
- So I guess you came here for nothing.
- I disagree.

1437
01:36:06.136 --> 01:36:08.263
I think you know more
than you're letting on.

1438
01:36:08.347 --> 01:36:09.973
Too bad I don't smoke.

1439
01:36:11.558 --> 01:36:17.189
Well. most alcoholics turn to coffee
when they quit drinking.

1440
01:36:21.193 --> 01:36:22.194
